OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FDrugs, arms, and terror: A 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fhigh-profile defector on   
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5FKim's North Korea          
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The old habits of secrecy haven't left 
OL,6, Kim Kuk-song.                          
OL,8,FIt has taken weeks of discussions to   
OL,9,Fget an interview with him, and he's    
OL,10,Fstill worried about who might be       
OL,11,Flistening. He wears dark glasses for   
OL,12,Fthe camera, and only two of our team   
OL,13,Fknow what we think is his real name.   
OL,15,FMr Kim spent 30 years working his way  
OL,16,Fto the top ranks of North Korea's      
OL,17,Fpowerful spy agencies. The agencies    
OL,18,Fwere the "eyes, ears, and brains of the
OL,19,FSupreme Leader", he says.              
